#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:5
msgid "Running HTML files with emrun"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:7
msgid ""
"*emrun* is a command line tool that can run generated HTML pages via a "
"locally launched web server. This is helpful when using web browsers that "
"cannot run a generated **.html** file via a ``file://`` URL (e.g. by double-"
"clicking the file) because of the default browser CORS rules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:9
msgid ""
"*emrun* also enables all kinds of command-line automation, for example, "
"integrating unit tests into an Emscripten environment in a project build "
"farm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:12
msgid "Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:14
msgid "*emrun* supports the following uses:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:16
msgid ""
"Launch your Emscripten-generated HTML page in a web browser from the command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:17
msgid ""
"Capture application ``stdout`` and ``stderr`` streams during the run, and "
"print them to a terminal or log them to a file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:18
msgid ""
"Pass command-line arguments to the application and read them from ``GET`` "
"parameters in the launched URL, or ``argc`` and ``argv`` in ``main()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:19
msgid ""
"Detect when a launched application quits via a call to C's "
"``exit(returncode)``, then pass the specified return code to the terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:20
msgid ""
"Choose which installed browser to run, or even run a browser on an Android "
"device connected to the local computer through *adb*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:24
msgid "Quick how-to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:26
msgid "Using *emrun* is simple:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:28
msgid ""
"Rebuild your Emscripten application and add the ``--emrun`` :ref:`linker "
"flag <emcc-emrun>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:30
msgid ""
"This flag injects code into the generated :ref:`Module` to enable capture of "
"``stdout``, ``stderr`` and ``exit()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:32
msgid ""
"If you skip this step, you can still run any **.html** file with *emrun*, "
"but the capture will not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:34
msgid ""
"Open a terminal, navigate to the build output directory, and call ``emrun "
"page.html``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:36
msgid ""
"This will spawn a new web server to host the page and launch your default "
"system browser to visit that page. *emrun* will block until the page calls "
"``exit(returncode)``, after which it will quit back to shell with the given "
"process exit code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:40
msgid "Choosing the browser to run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:42
msgid ""
"The ``--browser <filename-or-browser-alias>`` command line option allows you "
"to launch an HTML file using a particular browser, by specifying either its "
"\"browser alias\" or the full path to its executable (if the flag is not "
"specified, the default system browser is launched)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:44
msgid ""
"To enumerate the list of browser aliases on your system, use the ``--"
"list_browsers`` command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:61
msgid ""
"For your browser to be detected, it should be installed in the default "
"install location on the system (``%ProgramFiles%`` on Windows and ``/"
"Applications/`` on macOS) or by adding it to the ``PATH`` for the current "
"user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:63
msgid ""
"You can pass the ``--browser <alias>`` option to launch with a given "
"browser. For example, to run the *Firefox Nightly* browser you would call:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:69
msgid "To launch using a browser's filename use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:75
msgid ""
"If you just want to launch a web server you can pass the ``--no_browser`` "
"command line flag. In this case *emrun* will run the server without spawning "
"the browser (this is similar to using a :ref:`local webserver <faq-local-"
"webserver>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:82
msgid "Security implications"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:84
msgid ""
"*emrun* spawns its own web server to host the target **.html** file. This "
"has the following security implications:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:86
msgid ""
"The web server is a generic file server that by default serves all files in "
"the directory where the **.html** file resides, and all directories under "
"that directory tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:87
msgid "The web server will be visible to other computers on the same network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:91
msgid "Controlling web server operation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:93
msgid ""
"The following command line flags control how *emrun* spawns the web server:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:95
msgid ""
"``--no_server``: Do not launch a web server. The target file is run via the "
"``file://`` protocol, if possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:96
msgid ""
"``--serve_after_close``: Do not quit *emrun*; continue running the server "
"even after the user closes the web browser. Use this flag when you want to "
"visit the page multiple times or with different browsers during the same run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:97
msgid ""
"``--serve_after_exit``: Do not quit *emrun*; continue running the server "
"after the page finishes with a call to ``exit(returncode)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:98
msgid ""
"``--serve_root <path>``: Specify a custom directory to use as the root "
"directory for the spawned web server. By default, the directory where the **."
"html** file resides is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:99
msgid ""
"``--port <number>``: Specify the web server TCP port. The default port is "
"``6931``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:100
msgid ""
"``--silence_timeout <seconds>``: Specify the *emrun* silence timeout. If the "
"application does not print anything to ``stdout`` or ``stderr`` in this many "
"seconds, the page/browser is assumed to be hung, and *emrun* will quit. This "
"is disabled by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:101
msgid ""
"``--timeout <seconds>``: Specify the *emrun* timeout. If the whole page run "
"lasts longer than this many seconds, the page/browser is assumed to be hung, "
"and *emrun* will quit. This is disabled by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:102
msgid ""
"``--hostname <name>``: Specify the web server TCP hostname. The default "
"hostname is ``localhost``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:103
msgid ""
"``--timeout_returncode <code>``: Specifies the process return code that "
"*emrun* quits with if a page run timeout occurs. By default this is "
"``99999``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:107
msgid "Controlling log output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:109
msgid "The following command line flags affect logging output:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:111
msgid "``--verbose``: Print detailed information about *emrun* internal steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:112
msgid ""
"``--log_stdout <filename>``: Write all ``stdout`` messages from the "
"application to the named file (instead of printing to terminal)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:113
msgid ""
"``--log_stderr <filename>``: Write all ``stderr`` messages from the "
"application to the named file (instead of printing to terminal)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:114
msgid ""
"``--system_info``: Print detailed information about the current system "
"before launching. This is useful during automated runs when you want to "
"capture hardware information to logs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:115
msgid ""
"``--browser_info``: Print information about which browser is about to be "
"launched."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:116
msgid ""
"``--no_emrun_detect``: Hide the warning message that is launched if a target "
"**.html** file is detected to not have been built with ``--emrun``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:120
msgid "Cleaning up after the run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:122
msgid ""
"These command line flags allow you to clean up open browser processes before "
"starting a new run — this is important for automated testing on build "
"servers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:124
msgid ""
"``--kill_start``: Terminate all instances of the target browser process "
"before starting the run. Pass this flag to ensure that no old (hung) "
"instances of the target browser process exist that could interfere with the "
"current run. This is disabled by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:125
msgid ""
"``--kill_exit``: Terminate all instances of the target browser process when "
"*emrun* quits. Pass this flag to ensure that browser pages closed when the "
"run is over. This is disabled by default. Note that it may be necessary to "
"explicitly use the ``--browser=/path/to/browser`` command line option when "
"using ``--kill_exit``, or otherwise the termination might not function "
"properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:127
msgid ""
"These operations cause the browser process to be forcibly terminated.  Any "
"windows or tabs you have open will be closed, including any that might "
"contain unsaved data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:131
msgid "Running web pages in Firefox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:133
msgid ""
"When running web pages via ``emrun`` using Firefox, you may want to set one "
"or more of the following browser prefs: ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:166
msgid ""
"To set a Firefox browser pref, navigate to the page ``about:config`` in the "
"browser navigation bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:169
msgid "Running web pages on an Android device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:171
msgid "*emrun* can automate browser-based testing on Android."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:173
msgid "For this to work, you need to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:175
msgid ""
"Connect an Android phone to the local system via USB, with its developer "
"mode enabled. There is no need to root the phone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:176
msgid ""
"Install the *adb* tool on the host system and make sure it is present in the "
"``PATH`` environment variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:177
msgid ""
"Check that *adb* is working by calling ``adb devices`` to see that your "
"device is listed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:178
msgid "Install any browser apk to the device that you want to be able to run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:180
msgid ""
"To run on Android, add the ``--android`` command line flag and use the ``--"
"browser <alias>`` command line flag to explicitly choose the correct browser "
"to run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:182
msgid ""
"Omitting ``--browser`` (to launch a default Android browser) is not "
"supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:184
msgid "Running on Android will omit the ``--hostname`` option"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:186
msgid ""
"The following browser aliases have been tested and shown to work: ``firefox, "
"firefox_beta, firefox_aurora, firefox_nightly, chrome, chrome_beta, opera``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:188
msgid ""
"The following browser aliases are also supported, but have known issues:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:190
msgid ""
"``opera_mini``: The browser launches, but for some reason it times out when "
"trying to load any page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:191
msgid "``dolphin``: Works, but does not support WebGL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/compiling/Running-html-files-with-emrun.rst:193
msgid ""
"Otherwise, using *emrun* for browser-based testing on Android is the same as "
"when testing on the host system."
msgstr ""
